he prompt is looking for guidance beyond just the scaffold. It’s possible to include instructions without deterministic entries, leading me to consider whether the action should be no_action. Should the output include agent guidance on using in-test stubs instead of an external provider or database? I think the guidance might be useful even if it's advisory, especially regarding environment variables and properties for test-code setup. Ultimately, the question will guide the setup decision.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"jakarta.persistence-api is an API-only artifact; its only Maven dependency is the normal transitive compile dependency on jakarta.annotation-api, and meaningful API coverage can be reached with annotations, SPI/resolver stubs, and in-test EntityManager/Query implementations without a real JPA provider, database, Docker image, or system properties.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Do not add Hibernate, EclipseLink, H2, or a database container just to compile or exercise the API. Keep coverage focused on the Jakarta Persistence API surface using in-test stubs/fakes. For 4.0.0-M5, Query and TypedQuery include the new setParameters(Object...) method, so any local Query/TypedQuery test doubles must implement it.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"A generated integration-style test that calls Persistence.createEntityManagerFactory without installing a fake PersistenceProviderResolver or adding a real provider will fail because the API artifact does not include an implementation.\",\n    \"Adding a real provider/database would shift coverage toward the provider rather than the jakarta.persistence-api artifact and is not required for the reported javac failure.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04dd7909380038a5016a3e90098b608190a679468bb2f4168e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1889